text: Hua Yu Tseng (born 28 December 1977) is a Taiwanese volleyball player. She played for the Chinese Taipei women's national volleyball team. She played at the 2006 FIVB Volleyball Women's World Championship and 2006 Asian Games. She played for Taipei Physical Education College's women's volleyball team. == References == Category:1977 births Category:Living people Category:Taiwanese volleyball players
